        <p class="impact-footnote">Stats based on 2019-2025 LLP Events shows.</p>
    </section>

    {/* FAQ Section */}
    <section class="faq-section" data-scroll>
        <div class="faq-container">
            <div class="section-header">
                <h2 class="section-title">FREQUENTLY ASKED QUESTIONS</h2>
                <div class="title-underline"></div>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-grid">
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-answer-1">
                        <span>Where do I buy tickets?</span>
                        <span class="faq-icon" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
                    </button>
                    <div class="faq-answer" id="faq-answer-1" role="region">
                        <p>Tickets to our shows are typically available both online and at the venue box office. Buying on the web will often mean extra dollars in ticket fees, which will increase the advertised price. If a show does not require a ticket, it should be noted in all publicity.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-answer-2">
                        <span>What are the age restrictions?</span>
                        <span class="faq-icon" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
                    </button>
                    <div class="faq-answer" id="faq-answer-2" role="region">
                        <p>LLP Events believes that live music should be a family affair, so we do our best to keep the shows All Ages. This may not always be the case. Check individual show listings and <a href="#get-in-touch">contact us</a> if you need to double-check for peace of mind.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-answer-3">
                        <span>Where are the shows held?</span>
                        <span class="faq-icon" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
                    </button>
                    <div class="faq-answer" id="faq-answer-3" role="region">
                        <p>LLP Events built their shows and fanbase at Headliners Music Hall in Louisville, KY, and will always consider it home. That said, shows may sometimes take place in other venues and in other cities. Check individual show listings for details.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-answer-4">
                        <span>What's your refund policy?</span>
                        <span class="faq-icon" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
                    </button>
                    <div class="faq-answer" id="faq-answer-4" role="region">
                        <p>All sales are final. If a show is cancelled, you should receive an automatic refund (online purchase) or be able to return your ticket at the point of purchase. If a show is postponed, existing tickets will be honored at a later date. Contact the venue if you aren't able to attend the rescheduled date.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-answer-5">
                        <span>Can I bring a camera?</span>
                        <span class="faq-icon" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
                    </button>
                    <div class="faq-answer" id="faq-answer-5" role="region">
                        <p>Phones and point-and-click devices are allowed. If you want to bring a professional camera, please apply for a photo pass. <a href="#get-in-touch">Contact us here</a>.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-answer-6">
                        <span>Is there parking available?</span>
                        <span class="faq-icon" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
                    </button>
                    <div class="faq-answer" id="faq-answer-6" role="region">
                        <p>Parking will vary by venue. At Headliners, there is a pay lot next door and street parking on sections of Lexington and Payne Streets. Riding with a pal is always a good idea.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-answer-7">
                        <span>Will merch be available at the shows?</span>
                        <span class="faq-icon" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
                    </button>
                    <div class="faq-answer" id="faq-answer-7" role="region">
                        <p>Yes! We love seeing you in our shirts and gear. You'll find merch tables for LLP Events and many of the individual projects of the bands and artists performing inside the venue. Tip your merch person, too. (And if you want merch AFTER the show, <a href="#get-in-touch">contact us</a> and we will see what we have left.)</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-answer-8">
                        <span>Are venues accessible?</span>
                        <span class="faq-icon" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
                    </button>
                    <div class="faq-answer" id="faq-answer-8" role="region">
                        <p>We strive to make all LLP Events as inclusive as possible. This means not just an accessible section of seating, but often ASL interpreters. Check the venue's website for arrival preferences and policies if you plan to use the accessible amenities. <a href="#get-in-touch">Contact us</a> with any questions or concerns. And let us know if you have ideas on other ways we can make our shows more inclusive and welcoming.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-answer-9">
                        <span>How can I get involved with the show?</span>
                        <span class="faq-icon" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
                    </button>
                    <div class="faq-answer" id="faq-answer-9" role="region">
                        <p>We're always looking for talented musicians, vocalists, and crew members to join our shows. If you're interested in performing, helping backstage, or contributing in other ways, fill out our <a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLScbNnu_XmfKOQ5eOjW_uxrxUKiG35pSHufyXnfEf8B1ejQn-A/viewform?usp=header" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">application form</a>.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
    {/* Get In Touch Section */}
    <section id="get-in-touch" class="contact-standalone-section" data-scroll>
        <div class="contact-standalone-container">
            <h2 class="section-title">GET IN TOUCH</h2>
            <div class="title-underline"></div>

            <div class="contact-form-wrapper">
                <div id="contact-form-body" class="contact-form-body">
                    <form id="contact-form" class="contact-form">
                        <div class="form-row">
                            <div class="form-group">
                                <label for="contact-name">Name</label>
                                <input type="text" id="contact-name" name="name" placeholder="Your full name" required>
                            </div>
                            <div class="form-group">
                                <label for="contact-email">Email</label>
                                <input type="email" id="contact-email" name="email" placeholder="your@email.com" required>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="form-group">
                            <label for="contact-message">Message</label>
                            <textarea id="contact-message" name="message" rows="2" placeholder="How can we help?" required></textarea>
                        </div>
                        <div class="turnstile-wrapper">
                            <div class="cf-turnstile" data-sitekey="0x4AAAAAAB6pNVI-LTaMHdd8" data-theme="dark" data-error-callback="onTurnstileError"></div>
                        </div>
                        <button type="submit" id="contact-submit-btn" class="contact-submit-btn">Send Message</button>
                        <div id="contact-form-message" class="form-message" style="display: none;"></div>
                    </form>
                </div>
                <div id="contact-success-body" class="contact-success-body" style="display: none;">
                    <div class="success-icon" aria-hidden="true">✓</div>
                    <h3>Thank You!</h3>
                    <p>Thanks for reaching out. We'll get back to you as soon as possible.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    {/* Conditional Turnstile loader (production only) */}
    <script is:inline>
        if (window.location.hostname !== 'localhost' && window.location.hostname !== '127.0.0.1') {
            const loadTurnstile = () => {
                const script = document.createElement('script');
                script.src = 'https://challenges.cloudflare.com/turnstile/v0/api.js';
                script.async = true;
                script.defer = true;
                document.body.appendChild(script);
            };
            if ('requestIdleCallback' in window) {
                requestIdleCallback(loadTurnstile, { timeout: 2000 });
            } else {
                setTimeout(loadTurnstile, 1000);
            }
        }
    </script>
    <script src="/scripts/main.js" is:inline defer></script>
    <script src="/scripts/countdown.js" is:inline defer></script>
    <script src="/scripts/scroll-progress.js" is:inline defer></script>
    <script type="module" src="/scripts/newsletter.js" is:inline></script>
    <script type="module" src="/scripts/contact.js" is:inline></script>
    <script type="module" src="/scripts/analytics-tracking.js" is:inline></script>
    <script src="/scripts/social-proof.js" is:inline defer></script>
    <script defer src="/_vercel/insights/script.js" is:inline></script>
</BaseLayout>
